<p>„Maximize research usage and impact by maximizing user access to it.“</p>
<p>PIK and Leibniz Association support ‚Open Access‘. Open access maximizes the visibility of your work. This means also a potential higher impact of your research results.</p>
<p>With signing a contract with publishers of subscription journals, normally you give away all rights for re-use. Often publishers grant you some rights to republish your work but apply restrictions.</p> 
<p>Furthermore the German Copyright law since 01.01.2014 grants you as an author the right to make your final manuscript version accessible 12 month after publication (§ 38 Abs. 4 UrhG).</p>
<p>This means in many cases we can make your work accessible, mostly as ‘final draft’ (<a href="http://bib.telegrafenberg.de/en/publishing/open-access/final-draft/">http://bib.telegrafenberg.de/en/publishing/open-access/final-draft/</a>) via our institutional repository, the PIK publication database <a href="https://publications.pik-potsdam.de/">https://publications.pik-potsdam.de/</a>.</p>
<p>Please send  a final draft version of your article to <a href="mailto:library@pik-potsdam.de">library@pik-potsdam.de</a></p>
<p>The library will take care of legal restrictions and make your work, if possible, persistently open accessible worldwide.</p>
